sentence: Rita Pavone (Italian pronunciation: [ˈriːta paˈvoːne]; born August 23, 1945) is an Italian ballad and rock singer and actress, who enjoyed success through the 1960s.
In the United States she sang alongside Diana Ross and The Supremes, Ella Fitzgerald, Tom Jones, Duke Ellington, and Paul Anka.

It is said that Elvis Presley made a painting of her after she went to Memphis and met her at a recording studio.
It is also said that she recorded a duet with Barbra Streisand, but this has remained unsubstantiated.
Rita Pavone starred in six movies during the 1960s:
